    <bug_when>2015-03-06 11:20:47 -0800</bug_when>
    <thetext>When the spec uses quoted text to express a value of the String type, it usually uses &quot;neutral&quot; quotes (i.e. U+0022). Here are a few exceptions, where it uses “curly quotes” (U+201C and U+201D):

18.2.5 / step 12.a:  “0x”, “0X”

18.2.6.1.1 / step 4.d.vi.2: “%XY”

18.2.6.2 / step 3: “#”</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
